The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 November is 7,730 (894.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 November, there were 976 new confirmed cases (113.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 November, there were 878 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 11% ( 98 extra cases).
